hotspot.description: Rowan College of South Jersey - Cumberland Library is opening starting September 1, 2020 for students, Faculty and Staff by appointments only. The Hours are Mon-Thurs 10am-4pm and Friday 10am-3:30pm (until further notice). All reference services will be provided virtually through ZOOM, chat, and phone. The first hour 10am-11am, Mon-Fri, will be reserved for anyone who is compromised with health issues. Appointments can be made by filling out the above appointment request. The last appointment slot available will be 3:00pm Mon-Thurs and 2:30pm on Friday.
hotspot.title: Campus Book Store

hotspot.description: The One-Stop Enrollment Services counter provides customer service to current students, alumni and those wanting to start their college career at RCSJ – Cumberland. Students can complete everything in one visit. They can receive information about financial aid, enrollment, their student account, and set up a payment plan if needed. Students can request a transcript or an out of county charge back form, at the One Stop too. The One-Stop allows the student to get all their questions answered in one convenient location.
hotspot.title: One Stop Desk

hotspot.description: The Luciano Conference Center is home to our Business Studies Division. Offerings within the Center also include our spacious Banquet Room for academic lecture halls, as well as campus wide meetings and conferences. Our banquet room provides a versatile space and is fully equipped with up-to-date technology to include overhead projectors, large viewable screens, microphones and wifi.
hotspot.title: Conference Center

hotspot.description: The Frank Guaricini Fine and Performing Arts Center is a single-story building comprising a total conditioned floor area of 42,756 square feet. The original structure was built in 1992, with additions in 2002 and interior renovations in 2008. It houses classrooms, offices, black box studio, a theatre and gallery spaces. The Luciano Theatre in the Frank Guaricini, Jr. Fine and Performing Arts Center, is a 500-seat state of the art theatre and is home to our academic award-winning student productions featuring Broadway caliber plays and musicals as well as concerts by Bay Atlantic Symphony and the Vineland Regional Dance Company. The theatre has a complete fly system, adequate wing space and two adjacent dressing rooms to the stage.
hotspot.title: George Luciano Theatre
